## Code Style

### JavaScript
- Always use functional code patterns
- Always include JSDoc comments for all functions and classes
- Use ES6+ features (modules, classes, arrow functions, destructuring)
- Follow camelCase for variables and functions, PascalCase for classes
- Use const/let, never var
- Use static methods for component creation functions

### CSS/SCSS
- Always use CSS custom properties (variables) for design tokens
- Never hardcode color values, spacing, or typography
- Use utility classes for common patterns
- Follow kebab-case for class names
- Use SCSS partials for modularity

### HTML
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Include proper ARIA attributes for accessibility
- Use Bootstrap 4 classes for layout
- Use PLUS utility classes for styling
- Maintain consistent structure

### HTML Head Requirements
- **ALWAYS include Google Fonts in the `<head>` section** - Font styles must be loaded before CSS to ensure design tokens work correctly
- **ALWAYS include the following font links in every HTML file:**
```html
<!-- Google Fonts -->
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Lato:wght@300;400;600;700&family=Merriweather+Sans:wght@300;400;600;700&family=Open+Sans:wght@300;400;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
```
- **ALWAYS include Bootstrap 4.6.2 CSS** before PLUS Design System CSS
- **ALWAYS include Font Awesome** for icons
- **ALWAYS include PLUS Design System CSS** (`dist/css/main.css` or relative path)
- **Reference**: `templates/universal/html-head-template.html` for complete HTML head template
- **Never skip font loading** - missing fonts cause design tokens to default to system fonts

### Bootstrap Integration
- **ALWAYS use Bootstrap 4.6.2 as a foundation/base** - Bootstrap provides the functional structure and behavior
- **ALWAYS customize ALL styling to match Figma design EXACTLY** - Bootstrap's default appearance should be completely overridden
- **Bootstrap is ONLY for functional foundation** - use it for:
  - Component structure and HTML markup
  - JavaScript functionality (dropdowns, modals, etc.)
  - Grid system and layout utilities
  - Basic accessibility features
- **ALWAYS override ALL Bootstrap default styling** to match Figma exactly:
  - Override all default spacing/padding with design tokens
  - Override all default colors with design tokens
  - Override all default typography with design tokens
  - Override all default borders, shadows, and visual properties
- Bootstrap components (form-check, custom-control, dropdown, etc.) have default styling that must be completely replaced
- When using Bootstrap classes, explicitly override ALL visual properties:
  - Override `padding-left`, `padding-right`, `margin-left`, `margin-right` with design tokens
  - Override `background-color`, `color`, `border-color` with design tokens
  - Override `border-radius`, `box-shadow`, `font-size`, `line-height` with design tokens
  - Example: `.form-check` has default `padding-left: 1.25rem` - override with `padding-left: 0` and use `gap: var(--size-element-gap-sm)` instead
- Check Bootstrap's default styles and explicitly override ALL of them with PLUS tokens
- Never rely on Bootstrap's default visual styling - always use design tokens from Figma
- **Workflow**: 
  1. Use Bootstrap 4.6.2 as functional foundation (structure, behavior, JavaScript)
  2. Customize ALL styling to match Figma exactly (override every visual property)
  3. Use design tokens for all spacing, colors, typography, and visual properties
  4. Final result should look EXACTLY like Figma, not like Bootstrap

## Output Guidelines

### Code Generation
- **BEFORE generating code, ALWAYS:**
  1. **Check Figma first**: If a Figma link, selection, or component is provided:
     - **ALWAYS use Figma MCP tools** (`mcp_Figma_Desktop_get_design_context` and/or `mcp_Figma_Desktop_get_screenshot`) to see exactly what the Figma selection/link looks like - this is the FIRST step
     - **ALWAYS access Figma via Figma MCP** - never proceed without using MCP tools to view the design
     - **NEVER proceed without seeing the Figma design** - you must understand what it looks like before implementing
     - Study the Figma design system file or selection carefully after viewing it
     - Identify ALL variants shown in Figma
     - Note the exact text/content used in each variant
     - Measure spacing, colors, typography, and all visual properties
     - Implement EXACTLY as shown - pixel-perfect accuracy required
  2. **Study existing patterns:**
     - Review similar components in `design-system/components/` (atoms, molecules, organisms)
     - Review similar styles in `design-system/styles/`
     - **Reference production repository**: Check the cloned repository at `{cloned-repo-path}/java/docroot/javascript/pl2/plus_components/` for existing component implementations
       - Study production code patterns for functionality, event handling, and DOM structure
       - Match production implementation patterns exactly (naming, structure, behavior)
     - **Reference production SCSS**: Check `{cloned-repo-path}/java/sass/` for existing styling patterns
       - Study production SCSS patterns for class naming, structure, and token usage
       - Match production styling patterns exactly (class prefixes, organization, patterns)
  3. **Use Bootstrap 4.6.2 as foundation**: Start with Bootstrap 4.6.2 components for functional structure/behavior, then customize ALL styling to match Figma exactly
  4. **Match the exact structure, naming, and patterns used in existing code**
- Generate clean, readable code that matches existing patterns
- Include all necessary imports
- Use proper error handling
- Include JSDoc comments (match format: `@fileoverview`, `@param {Object} options`, `@returns {HTMLElement}`)
- Use design tokens consistently
- Ensure code is production-ready
- **Always reference guideline files** when in doubt

### Code Organization
- **Match existing code structure patterns:**
  - **JavaScript components**: Study `design-system/components/` (atoms, molecules, organisms) for patterns
    - Use named exports: `export function createComponentName()`
    - Use options object pattern: `{param1, param2, param3 = defaultValue}`
    - Import constants from `constants.js` when available
    - Use `document.createElement()` for DOM elements
    - Return HTMLElement (not HTML string)
  - **CSS/SCSS styles**: Study `design-system/styles/*.scss` for patterns
    - Use class prefixes matching existing: `.plus-*` for components, `.pbtn-*` for buttons
    - Use `color-mix(in srgb, ...)` for state layers (hover, active, focus)
    - Use `calc()` when adjusting for borders: `calc(var(--size-*) - 1px)`
    - Include comments explaining Figma references: `/* Figma: ... */`
    - Use `:not(:disabled):not(.disabled)` pattern for interactive states
  - **Production repository patterns**: Reference the cloned repository at `{cloned-repo-path}/java/docroot/javascript/pl2/plus_components/` for JavaScript component implementations and `{cloned-repo-path}/java/sass/` for SCSS styling patterns
- Group related code together
- Use meaningful variable names matching existing patterns
- Keep functions focused and small
- Use comments to explain complex logic
- Follow the established file structure
- **When in doubt, find the most similar existing file and match its structure**

## Testing Considerations

When generating code, consider:
- Does it work across different browsers?
- Is it responsive?
- Is it accessible?
- Does it use design tokens correctly?
- Does it follow PLUS patterns?
- Is it production-ready?
- Does it reference the appropriate guideline files?

## Anti-Patterns to Avoid

1. **Never hardcode colors**: ❌ `color: #00658e` ✅ `color: var(--color-primary)`
2. **Never hardcode spacing or use primitives**: ❌ `padding: 16px` ❌ `padding: var(--size-space-300)` ✅ `padding: var(--size-card-pad-x-md)`
3. **Never mix primitives with semantics**: Always use semantic tokens (primitives are infrastructure, not for direct use)
4. **Never use wrong semantic layer**: Match token to component context (Cards → `card-*` tokens, Sections → `section-*` tokens)
5. **Never use element-gap-xs for anything except label-to-input spacing**: This token is reserved for form label-input spacing only
6. **Never ignore element typography hierarchy**: Use H3→lg, H6→md, B3→sm for element spacing
7. **Never skip JSDoc**: Always document functions and classes
8. **Never ignore accessibility**: Always include ARIA attributes
9. **Never skip responsive design**: Always consider different screen sizes
10. **Never create components from scratch**: Use existing PLUS components when possible
11. **Never use inline styles for design tokens**: Use CSS variables and utility classes
12. **Never mix semantic sizes for same token type**: Use consistent sizes
13. **Never rely on Bootstrap default spacing**: ❌ Using Bootstrap's default `form-check` padding ✅ Override with `padding-left: 0` and use `gap: var(--size-element-gap-sm)`
14. **Never assume Bootstrap spacing matches design tokens**: Always explicitly override Bootstrap defaults with PLUS design tokens from Figma
15. **Never rely on Bootstrap's default appearance**: ❌ Using Bootstrap's default styling ✅ Bootstrap is foundation only - customize ALL styling to match Figma exactly
16. **Never make up text/content**: ❌ Inventing placeholder text ✅ Use EXACT text/content from Figma
17. **Never skip variants**: ❌ Implementing only one variant ✅ Implement ALL variants shown in Figma
18. **Never approximate Figma designs**: ❌ "Close enough" implementation ✅ Pixel-perfect match to Figma
19. **Never ignore Figma links/selections**: If provided, Figma takes absolute priority over assumptions
20. **Never implement without seeing the Figma design**: ❌ Guessing what a Figma link looks like ✅ ALWAYS use Figma MCP tools (`mcp_Figma_Desktop_get_design_context` and/or `mcp_Figma_Desktop_get_screenshot`) to see exactly what it looks like first
21. **Never skip font loading in HTML head**: ❌ Missing Google Fonts links ✅ ALWAYS include font links in `<head>` section
22. **Never create data visualizations without Highcharts**: ❌ Missing Highcharts CDN ✅ ALWAYS include Highcharts CDN links when creating charts
23. **Never use incorrect component import paths**: ❌ Wrong relative path ✅ ALWAYS verify import path based on prototype location
24. **Never hardcode table styling**: ❌ Hardcoded padding/spacing ✅ ALWAYS use table design tokens (`--size-table-cell-x`, `--size-table-cell-y`, etc.)
25. **Never hardcode elevation (box-shadow)**: ❌ Custom box-shadow values ✅ ALWAYS use elevation tokens (`--elevation-light-1` through `--elevation-light-5`)
26. **Never ignore table color states**: ❌ Custom table button colors ✅ ALWAYS use table color state tokens (Default, Hover, Pressed, Focus, Disabled) from `design-system/styles/colors.md`

## Remember

- **ALWAYS use design tokens** - no hardcoded values, ever
- **ALWAYS check Figma first** - if a Figma link/selection is provided, use Figma MCP tools (`mcp_Figma_Desktop_get_design_context` and/or `mcp_Figma_Desktop_get_screenshot`) to see exactly what it looks like BEFORE implementing
- **ALWAYS access Figma via Figma MCP** - never implement without viewing the Figma selection/link first using Figma MCP tools
- **ALWAYS see the Figma design** - never implement without viewing the Figma selection/link first using Figma MCP design context or screenshot tools
- **ALWAYS implement all variants** - list and create every variant shown in Figma
- **ALWAYS use exact Figma content** - never make up text, use exactly what's shown
- **ALWAYS use Bootstrap 4.6.2 as foundation** - then customize ALL styling to match Figma exactly
- **Always reference guideline files** when designing UI components
- Always prioritize using design tokens over hardcoded values
- Always include JSDoc comments
- Always use existing components when possible
- Always consider accessibility and responsiveness
- Always follow PLUS design system patterns
- Always generate production-ready code
- **When designing a specific UI type, reference `design-system/components/overview.md` first**
- **When selecting tokens, reference `design-system/styles/`** - Complete token reference organized as Icons/Colors/Typography/Layout/Elevation
